# Linting & Formatting

ALL code MUST pass ESLint, Prettier, and Stylelint before commit.

## ESLint

`@primer-guidy/eslint-config` exports two presets:

| Preset | Used by | Import |
|--------|---------|--------|
| `base` | Web apps, shared libs, components | `import { base } from '@primer-guidy/eslint-config'` |
| `nestServer` | NestJS server apps, `libs/nest-shared` | `import { nestServer } from '@primer-guidy/eslint-config'` |

### Shared Rules (both presets)

- `@typescript-eslint/strict` preset
- `no-explicit-any`: error
- `no-unused-vars`: error (args/vars/caught errors prefixed `_` are exempt, rest siblings allowed)
- `no-unused-expressions`: error
- `consistent-type-imports`: error (use `import type`)
- `no-magic-numbers`: error (raw numeric literals MUST be extracted into named constants — tests excluded). The constant definition itself (`const ICON_SIZE = 20`) is allowed; the violation is using the raw number inline (`size={20}`).
- `no-console`: warn (use logger utilities)

### `base` — Additional Rules (React)

- React rules: `react-hooks/exhaustive-deps`, `react/no-array-index-key`

### `nestServer` — Additional Rules (NestJS)

- `no-extraneous-class`: off for `*.module.ts` (NestJS modules are empty decorated classes)
- `consistent-type-imports`: off for `*.controller.ts`, `*.service.ts`, `*.guard.ts` (NestJS DI with `emitDecoratorMetadata` requires runtime imports)

### Adding a New Server

```javascript
// eslint.config.mjs — for any NestJS server
import { nestServer } from '@primer-guidy/eslint-config'

export default [...nestServer]
```

## Prettier

Consistent formatting across the monorepo:

- `singleQuote: true`
- `semi: false`
- `trailingComma: 'all'`
- `printWidth: 100`
- `tabWidth: 2`
- `arrowParens: 'always'`

## Stylelint

SCSS Module files MUST pass Stylelint:

- `stylelint-config-standard-scss` preset
- `declaration-no-important`: error
- `property-disallowed-list`: margin (all forms)
- `declaration-strict-value`: colors, font-size, font-weight, line-height, border-radius, box-shadow, z-index MUST use tokens/variables
- `selector-class-pattern`: camelCase (CSS Modules convention)
- `no-descending-specificity`: error

## Pre-commit

- All three tools run on staged files via lint-staged + husky
- CI pipeline MUST fail on any lint/format violation
- NEVER disable lint rules with inline comments unless reviewed and justified
